  "optimization_notes": "Root cause: hot time is dominated by main_scan doing row-wise predicate evaluation across most of num because ddate zonemap pruning is coarse, so work is not proportional to rows reaching anti-join/output. Strategy category C (work elimination) with plan restructuring: drive the scan from num_uom_hash posting rowids for USD, prune those rowids by zonemap candidate blocks before touching ddate/value, and fuse ddate+value filtering with anti-join probe and aggregation in one pass to remove intermediate survivor materialization and reduce memory traffic and scheduling overhead.",
